  "prompt": "How do I change my father and mother name which is misspelt in my birth certificate?",
  "response": "To change your parents' names on your birth certificate due to misspelling, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Gather Required Documents:\n- Original birth certificate\n- Proof of misspelling (affidavit, supporting documents)\n- Government-issued photo ID\n- Proof of parentage\n\n2. Contact Local Vital Records Office:\n- Typically located in the county or state where you were born\n- Each jurisdiction has specific procedures\n\n3. Obtain Correction Application:\n- Request a birth certificate amendment form\n- Fill out the form accurately\n- Provide supporting documentation\n\n4. Pay Required Fees:\n- Amendment fees vary by jurisdiction\n- Prepare to pay processing charges\n\n5. Submit Application:\n- Send documents to vital records office\n- Some offices allow in-person, mail, or online submissions\n\n6. Wait for Processing:\n- Processing time varies by location\n- May take several weeks\n\nAdditional Tips:\n- Consult local vital records office for exact requirements\n- Some jurisdictions might require court order\n- Ensure all documents are current and original\n- Keep copies of all submitted documents\n\nSpecific requirements can vary by state/country, so contact your local vital records office for precise instructions.",
